An Is yr. old robber pushedhis
luck too far Wednesday night.
The excellent memory of taxi
dispatcher caused a would be
robber to be trapped.


Paul Springs said he was rob-
bed of almost $24 by two men
when he answered a call at 10th
Street and Roeser Sept. 9.


George Peterson, taxi dis
patcher, had taken that call and
he received another call for the
same location. He recognized the
voice and telephoned police. de-
tectives watched the cab and
arrested two passengers.


One of the passengers William
Harris, 10, 274O E. Wier, adj
mitted robbing Springs and the
Aug. E robbery of another taxi
driver.

4McCOMB,. Miss. The home
Of Negro civil rights worker and
another Negro church were
bombed Saturday night. Enraged
Negroes stoned a police car when
1t drove into the area.


Mrs. Aylene Ouin, restaurant
owner and civil rights leader, re-
ported her two children, ages 9
and 5 were not seriously in
jured. A bomb was thrown in
front of her five room frame
house. Damages we're estimated
at $4,000.


The Society Hill Baptist Church
was demolished by fire about an
hour after the Quin home was
bombed. twas empty at the time.

CHICAGO = Congressman Will
liam L. Dawson, Democrat, was
honored during a testimonial
banquet held last week. DR.. Percy
L. Julian, chemist, was the main
speaker.


Mayor Richard Daley and many
others commended Dawson for
his service and leadership and
congratulated him for serving
in Congress for more than a
decade.

Ibrahim Mohamed Ibrahim, SUI
dams Deputy Director of Works.
is undertaking 2 p month tour
of U. S. highway departments
sponsored by its International
Developments Office of Inter-
national Training.


Mr.. Ibrahim will be in the
state Sept. 28-Oct. 2.


Ibrahim said, 81 would like to
see construction methods and
the maintenance of highways in
the different states, especially
in those states where the eli
mate is similar to ours"


Sudan's ten year development
program, according to Ibrahim.
calls for the construction of ap-
proximately 1000 kilometers of
roads. 1--WE expect to start on the
first one in two years time"
he revealed. "When / return,
l would like to put into practice
some of the things I'll see. Our
biggest project to date is the $50
kilometer road between Khar-
toum and Wad Medani.''

CLEVELAND = Singer Gloria
Lynne was wounded by a stray
bullet during a gun fight between
policemen and a bandit. The
singer was appearing at down.
town entertainment spot, Leo's
Casino and had just made her
entrance.


Miss Lynne will remain at
home for the next two weeks.
She was not seriously injured.
